                                            Apple TV+ may now be known as Apple TV, but it still offers a weekly selection of great movies to watch.  
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>This week's roundup of great movies to watch comes with a bit of news specific to this particular streaming service. In <a href="https://www.apple.com/tv-pr/news/2025/10/apple-original-films-blockbuster-feature-f1-the-movie-from-joseph-kosinski-to-make-global-streaming-debut-on-friday-december-12-2025/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">a press release</a> announcing the premiere date of <em>F1 The Movie</em>, <a href="https://shop-links.co/link/?exclusive=1&publisher_slug=howtogeek&u1=UUhtgUeUpU2017312&article_name=5+Apple+TV+Movies+You+Should+Stream+This+Week+%28October+13+-+19%29&article_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Fapple-tv-plus-movies-stream-this-week-october-13%2F&url=https%3A%2F%2Ftv.apple.com%2F" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">Apple TV+</a> has quietly changed its name, dropping the "+" and is now just "Apple TV."</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 13 Oct 2025 20:30:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/apple-tv-plus-movies-stream-this-week-october-13/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The Naya Create Is the Specialty Keyboard System for When Time and Money Are No Object]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/naya-create-review/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Bill Loguidice]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/10/01-2025-10-09-13-10-03.jpg" length="946" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Naya Create]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Naya Create is a premium modular keyboard system that encourages a new way to work. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>In a sea of me-too keyboard and mouse designs, it's refreshing when a product like the <a href="https://naya.tech/products/naya-create-3-0" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Naya Create</a> attempts to break the mold. Unfortunately, this modular keyboard system proves more enthusiast's experiment than something that's ready for the mass market.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 13 Oct 2025 20:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/naya-create-review/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Your PC Feels Slow? Microsoft Says These Two Windows 11 Settings Are to Blame]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/your-pc-feels-slow-microsoft-says-these-two-windows-11-settings-are-to-blame/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Aman Kumar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/windows_11_generic_hero_1-jpg.jpg" length="136116" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows 11]]></category><category><![CDATA[OneDrive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Configure these settings for a performance boost.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Everyone wants their Windows PCs to offer the best performance. Apps should open instantly, there shouldn't be any lag when switching windows, and the system itself should boot immediately. However, if any of these aspects feel a bit sluggish, Microsoft says it could be due to your OneDrive file syncing settings and your computer's visual effects.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 13 Oct 2025 20:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/your-pc-feels-slow-microsoft-says-these-two-windows-11-settings-are-to-blame/</guid></item></channel>
